<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL RIDE OPTIMIZED SUSPENSION (IROS) - component removal - TORQUE RODS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>TORQUE RODS</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0301325">Figure 25</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <para>It may not be necessary to remove the chassis suspension torque rod during IROS replacement procedures. It
            is advised to check the axle bracket boss for excessive wear, and replace if needed. Inspect all parts for
            wear, cracking or failed welds. Repair or replace as needed.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the torque rod assembly, locate the bushing mounting bolts and nuts at the frame
                rail mounting bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the mounting bolts. Check any shims or spacers for wear or damage.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the torque rod bushing mounting bolts and nuts at the axle housing bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the torque rod mounting bolts and nuts. Inspect the axle boss for
                excessive wear. Replace if needed.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0301325" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301325.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 25. Torque Rod Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. TORQUE ROD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. TORQUE ROD FRAME RAIL MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>3. REINFORCING PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. TORQUE ROD AXLE MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>5. FRAME RAIL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove torque rod.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Note the position and quantity of alignment spacers for reassembly.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
